{
  "texts": [
    "Advances in AI provide an unprecedented ability to analyze these complex interactions, enabling more efficient and predictive tools in foods, health, and related domains.",
    "Traditional methods for olfactory and gustatory research relied heavily on subjective sensory panel assessments and chemical analysis (Torrico et al. 2023).",
    "These methods faced limitations due to human variability, scalability, and precision.",
    "The advent of artificial intelligence (AI), particularly machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), has significantly transformed the field (LeCun et al. 2015).",
    "The integration of AI into sensory research has followed a clear trajectory over the past few decades."
  ]
}